&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POST:                               &lt;/strong&gt;Staff Nurse Band 5/Registered Nursing Associate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOCATION:                      Stannon HCE (old Shipley)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS:                            &lt;/strong&gt;37.5hrs Days Nights Weekends         &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We on Stannon HCE provide a wonderful caring environment for both patients and staff with a focus on ensuring the safety and holistic well-being of elderly patient’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Registered Nurses with a passion and commitment for looking after older people. As a Registered Nurse/Nursing Asscociate on Stannon Ward you will find it extremely rewarding and stimulating, you will also find opportunities to develop your skills, professional expertise and be the est nurse you can be. The Stannon team pride themselves on being committed to excellence in the direct medical intervention and compassionate health care, we lead on innovation and welcome change. Come and join our team and be inspired and progress your career. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Charge Nurse Matthew Potter&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mpotter1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01752 432671/01752 431388 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is intended that the interviews will take place within 3 weeks of the closing date therefore if you have not heard from us by this time; you may assume that you have not been successful.  The interview will be held on Merrival Ward, Lv 10 , in the mangers office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plymouth Hospitals NHS Trust is an equal opportunities employer and is working towards a smoke-free environment.  Under the Trust’s Green Commuter Strategy, on site parking is restricted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
